In re DUNNING. (Circuit Court of Appeals, First Circuit. April 23, 1903.) No. 476. Petition for Revision of Proceedings of the District Court of the United States for the District of Massachusetts, in Bankruptcy. E. S. Mansfield and George R. Swasey, for petitioner. Jeremiah Smith, Jr., for respondent.

Before COLT and PUTNAM, Circuit Judges, and ALDRICH, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

Petition dismissed by the court without prejudice and without costs, as per stipulation on file.
